The paper focuses on parallelizing deep convolutional neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new approach to optimizing the training process of neural networks. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as convolutional neural networks are commonly used in image and video analysis. The third category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper deals with parallelizing the training process across multiple devices. The fourth category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of neural networks. The fifth category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with improving the efficiency of a key component of AI systems.
